	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A Kenyan opposition politician says he is still detained in a toilet at the country's main airport after he refused an attempt to deport him. A lawyer for Miguna Miguna, James Orengo, says authorities are in contempt after the High Court on Tuesday ordered his immediate release and a court appearance on Wednesday morning. Miguna was deported to Canada last month in a crackdown on politicians who attended the mock inauguration of opposition leader Raila Odinga to protest President Uhuru Kenyatta's re-election. A court later ordered that his Kenyan passport be restored and that he be allowed to return. Miguna early on Wednesday posted a statement on social media saying he remained "detained inside a tiny and filthy toilet" in a terminal at Nairobi's international airport. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news from around the continent by
